{
  "texts": [
    "On its own NeRF is a 6D continuous vector function, where the inputs are ray coordinates.",
    "These ray coordinates are similar to points from a point cloud, which was converted from a depth image.",
    "The problem with the basic NeRF is that too much optimization is required for each scene, and new scenes are hardly generalizable.",
    "To solve the problem, starting from (Eslami et al. 2018), Kosiorek et al. (2021) mixed NeRF with VAE to create Neural Radiance Fields VAE (NeRF-VAE), the novelty of which is the ability to generate new scenes from a previously unseen environment.",
    "The NeRF-VAE learns a distribution over a radiance field by conditioning them into the latent space."
  ]
}